Ok this will be a bit so bear with me

Back in the day Dakkon knew a powerful walker named Geyadrone Dihada, who promised him the power of a planes walker in return for forging a weapon that drew strength from all energy, mana and life force.

Dakkon forged the weapon, traveling across the lands and forging it in different areas by using the mana from each area and finalizing the fold of the blade by plunging it into a powerful native to seal the energy.

She screwed him over, took the blade and locked his soul inside of it and gave it to Sol'kanar the swamp king and left dominaria. Dakkon went on a hunt for the blade, losing much of his humanity in the process and eventually took it back from Sol'kanar but not before the scheming Dihada came back to Dominaria and ignited Dakkon's spark unwittingly.
Is Dakkon dead now?
She screwed him over again by tricking a boy into doing a ritual that bound Dakkon to Dominaria, essentially to shield from his wrath and subjugate him as her champ.
Oh were getting there. This fool had a comic book and a short story. His shit gets real.

Dakkon said eff slavery and waged war on Dihada, this is chronologically after the thran and brother's war. The Blackblade-Dihada war lasted only a few days, but was violent and scarred the area of dominaria it occurred in.

Dakkon was unsuccessful in defeating her, and was marked ultimately as her champion. They disappeared, only to see Dihada return millenia later without Dakkon during the Planes walker war of Time Spiral and with Korlash holding the Blackblade.

It is unknown what happened to Dakkon after they planes walked from Dominaria, but Korlash's possession of the blade indicates Dakkon met his end somehow and that Korlash came into the blade by some means. This all needs to be filled in by the lore dept.
